FBIS4-32536 "dreeu123_y_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Kosovo Serb Convoy of 28 Tanks Moves Toward Podujeve Serb Convoy of 28 Tanks Moves Toward Podujeve AU2406191294 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 GMT 24 Jun 94 AU2406191294 Tirana TVSH Television Network Albanian BFN [Text] At about 0500 this morning, a Serbian Army convoy made up of 28 tanks and seven transportation trucks, as well as other military equipment, moved from Prishtina in the direction of Podujeve on the Miloshev-Leban road. A characteristic of the Serb Army movements this time is that many Serb flags were seen placed above the tanks. It is worthy of mention that in this region today, there were frequent flights by Serbian aircraft, and many military vehicles were observed on the streets of Prishtina, reports the Kosova Information Center.
